condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Additional Condition of Effectiveness | Description :The MoTC shall have selected a financial managementspecialist and a procurement specialist under TORs satisfactory to the Bank. The Project accounting system satisfactory to the Bankis in place, with in-built controls capable of tracking Project resources and expenditures and generating financial reports. TheBorrower has adopted the Project Operation Manuel acceptable to the Bank. | Due Date :31-Jul-2012

Finance Agreement :Institutional Arrangement: Operation and Maintenance Operational | Description :The Borrower shall cause theMoTC to commence operation and maintenance of the Road Corridor section between Kyzyl-Orda and Taraz, as determined under the pilotin Part 2 (a) of the Project, no later than three months after each sub-section of the road is opened to traffic and in accordancewith the respective Quality Charter. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Institutional Arrangements: RRA Team and MMU Operational | Description :The Borrower, through MoTC shall nolater than June 30, 2013 (i) appoint and establish the RRA team with a composition, resources and terms of reference satisfactoryto the Bank, and (ii) establish a Motorway Management Unit in form and substance satisfactory to the Bank. | Due Date :30-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :Institutional Arrangements: Quality Charter Developed | Description :The Borrower shall cause the MoTC, and KVD,to develop and endorse the Form Quality Charter for the pilot operation and maintenancescheme under Part 2 (a) of the Project nolater than June 30, 2013. | Due Date :30-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :Institutional arrangement: Assessment of Operation and Maintenance. | Description :The Borrower, through theMoTC shall no later than January 30, 2015 submit to the Bank an assessment of the operation and maintenance needs for the RoadsCorridor covering the period of at least 15 years from the date of the assessment for the purpose of assessing potential gaps infinancing the activities necessary to reach an acceptable level of service along the Corridor. | Due Date :30-Jan-2015

Finance Agreement :Project Reports: Annual Review | Description :No later than December 31, 2012, and annually thereafter, theBorrower, through the MoTC, shall carry out jointly with the Bank, annual reviews of the progress made in carrying out the Project.The Borrower, through the MoTC, shall prepare at least four (4) weeksprior to the annual reviews, and furnish to the Bank, aseparate report. | Frequency :Yearly
